{
  "texts": [
    "They work by projecting the onto hyperplanes that make the inference easier.",
    "Kernel methods can be used for supervised and unsupervised problems.",
    "A commonly used kernel-based method for classification is the support vector machine (SVM).",
    "Another common method in unsupervised settings is kernel principal component analysis (PCA), used for dimensionality reduction in order to facilitate clustering.",
    "Ensemble methods combine multiple ML models to produce an optimal model."
  ]
}